Docker - runs on top of os kernel/or the application layer.
        - Occupies less systems memory
        - Boots faster
        - Not compatible with windows system, requires WSL to run.
        
Virtual machine - runs on top of systems hardware/has its own os kernel
                  and application layer.
                - Occupies alot of systems memory.
                - Boots slowly, because every start have to launch the    entire OS.
                - Compatible with all OS.